gen_text:  The paper "Compressed quantum error mitigation" by Maurits Tepaske and David Luitz is about the mitigation of errors in quantum algorithms. The authors propose a method to mitigate errors in a quantum algorithm by applying a denoiser after the execution of the algorithm. The denoiser is a set of circuits that are sampled from a quasiprobability distribution. The authors show that efficient, local denoisers can be found, and demonstrate their effectiveness for the digital quantum simulation of the time evolution of simple spin chains. The authors also show that the denoiser recovers the noiseless expectation values from the noisy circuit. The authors conclude that the denoiser is able to mitigate errors to a large extent.
