gen_text:  The relationship between fishing effort and catch per unit effort (CPUE) is complex. The best fit model of CPUE per trip was significantly lower in January, and decreased with higher numbers of hooks, despite a higher total catch per trip and set. CPUE was also significantly higher for surface longlines than bottom longlines. CPUE of threatened and regulated species was also higher when fewer hooks were deployed.
